L.B. Foster Birmingham Coating Plant
 The L.B. Foster Coated 
							Products pipe coating plant is an ISO 9001:2008 
							Registered facility that applies FBE corrosion 
							protection, ARO overcoating and internal linings in 
							a modern state of the art manufacturing environment. 
							This facility is located on the site of American 
							Steel Pipe’s Birmingham, Alabama operations. 
 





L.B. Foster Willis, 
							TX Specialty Coating Plant
 The L.B. Foster Ball 
							Winch, Inc. plant can apply protective coatings to 
							1/2” through 94” diameter pipe and fabricated 
							products. Our pipe handling equipment has a lift 
							capacity up to 30,000 lbs. L.B. Foster has developed 
							proprietary equipment that provides the accuracy and 
							efficiency needed to exceed customer expectations. 








L.B. Foster Custom Coats Pipe, Induction Bends, 
						Forged Fittings and Field Joints
L.B. Foster offers 
						protective coatings for more than just straight 
						linepipe. We also provide a wide range of internal/external corrosion and abrasion protection for pipe, 
						fittings, risers, vessels and fabricated steel in 
						quantities from one to thousands. The L.B. Foster Ball 
						Winch plant coats unique steel products of most 
						sizes and pipe ranging from 1/2” through 94” with FBE, 
						liquid epoxy and other protective coatings.
 
Worldwide Projects
Our coated products are in 
				   use on major projects worldwide where quality coating is 
				   critical. The L.B. Foster team of coating professionals has 
				   built a reputation for satisfying the most demanding 
				   requirements for custom coated materials with quality 
				   applications and extraordinary logistical support. Our 
				   Houston-area facility can meet our customers’ most
				   exacting specifications and difficult schedules and provide 
				   quick turnaround for short run and emergency pipe coating 
				   projects.



